        "Non-Immigrant - Florida Department of Highway Safety and Motor Vehicles": "非移民 - Florida Department of Highway Safety and Motor Vehicles",
        "Nonimmigrant visa holders (F-1, H-1B, J-1, L-1, O-1, and others) face state-by-state variation in driver's license documents and REAL ID (often tied to I-94 / visa dates), in-state tuition (most public universities classify F-1 students as out-of-state), professional licensure documentation, tax residency rules, and health-insurance options. USCIS also requires reporting any address change within 10 days via Form AR-11.\n\nMoveSafe is not a substitute for legal counsel. Consider consulting a licensed immigration attorney, your school's DSO if on F-1, employer HR or immigration counsel if on a work visa, and a qualified tax professional for cross-state filing.": "非移民签证持有人(F-1、H-1B、J-1、L-1、O-1 及其他)面临州对州个差异,涉及驾照证件佮 REAL ID(常佮 I-94 / 签证日期挂钩)、本州学费(大部分公立大学将 F-1 学生分类为外州生)、专业执照文件、税务居住规则,以及健康保险选项。USCIS 嘛要求任何地址变更需在 10 工内透过表格 AR-11 报告。\n\nMoveSafe 毋是法律建议个替代品。建议咨询持证移民律师;若是 F-1 签证,请咨询学校个 DSO;若是工作签证,请咨询雇主 HR 或移民法律顾问;对跨州申报,请咨询有资格个税务专业人士。",
